 The (event(s) or object(s) that prove something) of decline 
 The relative decline of farming is clear from both thin sliceal and 
 time-series data for the major country groupings shown in Table 1. The negative relationships between agriculture's shares of gross domestic product 
 ( G D PSH), employment ( EMPSH) and exports ( EXPSH) on the one hand, 
 and income per person ( YPC) on the other, are very significant (related to numbers). 
 These shares are also negatively connected with population density per unit 
 of farming-based land ( PD), although significantly so only for EXPSH. This is 
 clear from the following OLS moving backward equation guesses, which are based 
 on World Bank data for 1981 for 70 countries with (groups of people/animals/things) more than 1 
